1
00:00:00,320 --> 00:00:03,440
If you let yourself go,
aren't pretty or fabulous,

2
00:00:03,880 --> 00:00:06,880
the world will forget you,
and you'll have no one.

3
00:00:07,172 --> 00:00:08,516
Just slow down, Ikkyu.

4
00:00:09,180 --> 00:00:10,493
Don't grow up so fast.

5
00:00:11,080 --> 00:00:13,522
"Kick him out of the group chat.
Stay away from him."

6
00:00:13,547 --> 00:00:15,012
"Ban Ikkyu." "Ban Ikkyu."

7
00:00:15,012 --> 00:00:16,012
"Stop."

8
00:00:16,037 --> 00:00:17,401
"Ban Ikkyu." "Ban Ikkyu."

9
00:00:17,426 --> 00:00:19,552
It feels good to get it out.

10
00:00:20,880 --> 00:00:23,723
- Are you thirsty?
- Nidnoi.

11
00:00:26,606 --> 00:00:28,680
- Want some water?
- Nidnoi.

12
00:00:29,920 --> 00:00:32,500
Don't you have any new ideas?

13
00:00:33,440 --> 00:00:34,440
I do.

14
00:00:35,494 --> 00:00:36,706
Of course I do.

15
00:00:36,731 --> 00:00:40,640
Famous cartoons
don't always make sense either.

16
00:00:41,400 --> 00:00:42,830
But they're fun.

17
00:00:43,401 --> 00:00:46,021
If you want to
tell a story, just do it.

18
00:00:46,021 --> 00:00:48,040
Don't get stuck on Kittima.

19
00:00:48,480 --> 00:00:52,840
Thank you for your great answer.

20
00:00:57,600 --> 00:00:59,163
"I can't sleep tonight."

21
00:00:59,880 --> 00:01:02,615
"Because memories from long ago..."

22
00:01:02,640 --> 00:01:04,930
"are waking from their slumber..."

23
00:01:05,594 --> 00:01:07,080
"and rousing me awake."

24
00:01:16,520 --> 00:01:17,720
Excuse me, everyone.

25
00:01:17,720 --> 00:01:19,200
For the next song,

26
00:01:19,224 --> 00:01:22,663
we are honored by
a two-time provincial champion.

27
00:01:23,400 --> 00:01:25,520
The man with the golden voice.

28
00:01:26,360 --> 00:01:28,760
Currently, he is our producer.

29
00:01:29,004 --> 00:01:32,520
Give it up for Thai.

30
00:01:32,520 --> 00:01:39,831
Woo! Woo!

31
00:01:39,831 --> 00:01:40,978
I don't sing anymore.

32
00:01:41,003 --> 00:01:43,175
Just a little bit.

33
00:01:43,200 --> 00:01:44,520
Just for fun, Thai.

34
00:01:44,520 --> 00:01:46,040
I haven't practiced.

35
00:01:46,065 --> 00:01:49,988
Come on, who rehearses for a party?

36
00:01:50,013 --> 00:01:52,643
Come on, sing for us.

37
00:01:52,668 --> 00:01:54,291
Please...

38
00:01:54,316 --> 00:01:56,800
Just a little bit.

39
00:01:56,825 --> 00:01:57,868
- Please.
- Come on, Thai.

40
00:01:57,893 --> 00:02:03,652
Thai, Thai.

41
00:02:03,652 --> 00:02:09,032
Thai, Thai.

42
00:02:09,032 --> 00:02:15,122
Woo woo!

43
00:02:16,435 --> 00:02:19,600
♪ In the shadows of the night ♪

44
00:02:21,160 --> 00:02:25,920
♪ I find my comfort in your sight ♪

45
00:02:26,513 --> 00:02:31,511
♪ The warmth that guides us ♪

46
00:02:31,535 --> 00:02:35,262
♪ Through the dark ♪

47
00:02:36,627 --> 00:02:41,655
♪ You are the light
that shines so bright ♪

48
00:02:41,680 --> 00:02:46,080
♪ You are the hope echoing inside ♪

49
00:02:46,751 --> 00:02:51,655
♪ You are the reason ♪

50
00:02:51,680 --> 00:02:54,523
♪ I find the morning light ♪

51
00:02:58,954 --> 00:03:00,760
- Hey!
- What?

52
00:03:11,844 --> 00:03:14,019
That was so cool, Thai.

53
00:03:14,019 --> 00:03:16,480
What a superstar aura!

54
00:03:18,255 --> 00:03:21,495
But the lyrics seem
to be on holiday tonight.

55
00:03:21,520 --> 00:03:24,675
Easy there. He's one of us.

56
00:03:24,700 --> 00:03:28,208
He knows I'm just teasing.

57
00:03:28,233 --> 00:03:29,233
Yeah.

58
00:03:32,408 --> 00:03:34,257
Cheers!

59
00:03:34,282 --> 00:03:35,319
Woo!

60
00:03:35,344 --> 00:03:37,000
Cheers! Cheers!

61
00:03:40,025 --> 00:03:41,375
Okay.

62
00:03:42,801 --> 00:03:45,121
Excuse me, are you Mr. Thai?

63
00:03:46,360 --> 00:03:47,360
Yes.

64
00:03:48,663 --> 00:03:51,291
Thai, I'm Ting.

65
00:03:51,316 --> 00:03:55,403
I'm Orn, Mr. Boon's student,
in the Rakang Kaew group.

66
00:04:03,920 --> 00:04:05,736
He has cancer.

67
00:04:07,584 --> 00:04:08,584
Cancer?

68
00:04:10,378 --> 00:04:11,378
Yes.

69
00:04:12,196 --> 00:04:13,600
We were all shocked.

70
00:04:15,160 --> 00:04:18,240
He's receiving palliative care now.

71
00:04:18,240 --> 00:04:20,095
At the same house.

72
00:04:20,120 --> 00:04:23,110
The one where we used to
stay when we were kids.

73
00:04:24,142 --> 00:04:25,142
Right.

74
00:04:26,740 --> 00:04:28,495
It's unbelievable.

75
00:04:28,520 --> 00:04:31,927
He always seemed invincible.

76
00:04:31,952 --> 00:04:35,280
The pillar who
supported and pushed us,

77
00:04:35,280 --> 00:04:38,410
the singers of
Rakang Kaew for decades.

78
00:04:39,182 --> 00:04:42,012
We're visiting him to
give him some support.

79
00:04:42,037 --> 00:04:43,623
You should come with us.

80
00:04:44,200 --> 00:04:48,120
He would be so happy
to see his students reunited.

81
00:04:51,877 --> 00:04:53,806
Orn, message me the details, okay?

82
00:04:53,831 --> 00:04:56,610
- Sure.
- I'll find something he likes too.

83
00:04:58,234 --> 00:04:59,423
Come with us, Thai.

84
00:05:14,787 --> 00:05:17,027
"Congratulations to Teacher Boon
on receiving the award!"

85
00:05:17,052 --> 00:05:18,085
"Congrats!"

86
00:05:18,109 --> 00:05:21,782
"Well deserved."

87
00:05:32,596 --> 00:05:34,596
And the award
you've all been waiting for...

88
00:05:35,360 --> 00:05:37,615
The Best Singer Award...

89
00:05:37,640 --> 00:05:41,389
in the New Star
Thai Country Music Contest...

90
00:05:41,414 --> 00:05:42,414
goes to...

91
00:05:48,955 --> 00:05:51,683
Thai Wongkatanyuta!

92
00:05:55,120 --> 00:05:57,080
Congratulations to Thai!

93
00:05:57,080 --> 00:05:59,394
On this occasion, we are honored by

94
00:05:59,418 --> 00:06:01,695
Teacher Boonmala Urairuang,

95
00:06:01,739 --> 00:06:05,151
a prolific composer and mentor.

96
00:06:05,176 --> 00:06:09,200
He will present the trophy
and a scholarship of 500 baht.

97
00:06:09,225 --> 00:06:10,397
Please welcome him!

98
00:06:17,080 --> 00:06:21,632
And this year winner

99
00:06:21,675 --> 00:06:25,181
will move into Mr. Boon's home,

100
00:06:25,206 --> 00:06:30,288
joining the Rakang Kaew project
to train as a professional singer!

101
00:06:30,313 --> 00:06:32,040
Congratulations to Thai,

102
00:06:32,040 --> 00:06:33,880
and his parents,

103
00:06:33,880 --> 00:06:37,368
for this opportunity.

104
00:06:37,368 --> 00:06:40,030
With his looks and voice,

105
00:06:40,055 --> 00:06:43,090
he'll go far for sure.

106
00:06:49,118 --> 00:06:50,131
Thai.

107
00:06:51,668 --> 00:06:52,668
Thai.

108
00:06:53,869 --> 00:06:54,869
Thai.

109
00:06:57,463 --> 00:06:59,000
- Thai.
- Hmm?

110
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:00,280
She's asking you a question.

111
00:07:02,320 --> 00:07:04,404
Cee, you can ask him again.

112
00:07:04,429 --> 00:07:08,290
How do I sing
high notes comfortably?

113
00:07:14,520 --> 00:07:16,196
To sing high notes...

114
00:07:16,720 --> 00:07:19,716
just think that
you're walking downwards.

115
00:07:20,480 --> 00:07:24,136
Like you're walking
down stairs comfortably.

116
00:07:25,680 --> 00:07:28,415
Wow, that's exactly it.

117
00:07:28,440 --> 00:07:30,840
Exactly what
my old teacher told me.

118
00:07:31,725 --> 00:07:33,205
Did it work?

119
00:07:33,205 --> 00:07:36,103
Well, it kind of worked.

120
00:07:36,587 --> 00:07:39,295
Did you go to
the same school as him?

121
00:07:39,320 --> 00:07:42,943
He studied at Boonmala's school.

122
00:08:01,375 --> 00:08:03,570
He wanted us
to stand in the rain or what?

123
00:08:05,360 --> 00:08:08,534
Those people are so loud.

124
00:08:08,559 --> 00:08:10,787
Wonder why he wanted to meet up?

125
00:08:10,812 --> 00:08:13,556
There he is.

126
00:08:14,160 --> 00:08:16,120
If you were any later,

127
00:08:16,120 --> 00:08:19,120
Ohn and I would have
sprouted roots in this rain.

128
00:08:20,240 --> 00:08:23,592
You said it was urgent.

129
00:08:23,617 --> 00:08:25,135
But you're late
to your own meeting?

130
00:08:25,160 --> 00:08:28,274
What's up with you?
I've been calling you all day.

131
00:08:28,299 --> 00:08:29,299
I'm sorry.

132
00:08:29,960 --> 00:08:33,036
I was in the studio all day,
so I silenced my phone.

133
00:08:34,935 --> 00:08:37,101
Let's go inside.
I have something to discuss.

134
00:08:37,126 --> 00:08:38,269
Cheers!

135
00:08:41,906 --> 00:08:42,986
Hmm...

136
00:08:47,834 --> 00:08:48,834
Mr. Boon...

137
00:08:50,045 --> 00:08:51,960
whose house you stayed at?

138
00:08:53,328 --> 00:08:56,895
The Rakang Tong, right?

139
00:08:56,920 --> 00:08:59,295
Rakang Kaew, Ohn.

140
00:08:59,320 --> 00:09:00,320
Yeah, that one.

141
00:09:01,883 --> 00:09:03,152
Hmm.

142
00:09:03,177 --> 00:09:05,307
Why are you worried
about visiting him?

143
00:09:06,639 --> 00:09:07,639
Oh!

144
00:09:08,484 --> 00:09:11,017
Or do you have a problem
with the person who invited you?

145
00:09:12,323 --> 00:09:14,575
- No.
- Hmm?

146
00:09:15,640 --> 00:09:16,640
- Chon.
- Huh?

147
00:09:17,676 --> 00:09:21,110
He looks more worried than usual.

148
00:09:22,535 --> 00:09:24,760
Is there something wrong? Or...

149
00:09:26,560 --> 00:09:27,560
Or what?

150
00:09:31,976 --> 00:09:34,156
The reason you
don't want to visit him

151
00:09:35,086 --> 00:09:38,522
is because of what
happened back then?

152
00:09:44,683 --> 00:09:50,163
- Thai.
- Hey Thai!

153
00:09:52,898 --> 00:09:55,318
He didn't come to
school or volleyball practice.

154
00:09:56,078 --> 00:09:57,078
Yeah.

155
00:09:58,646 --> 00:09:59,666
Thai!

156
00:10:00,598 --> 00:10:01,624
Hey, Thai!

157
00:10:07,760 --> 00:10:08,850
Looks like he's not home.

158
00:10:09,493 --> 00:10:11,076
Then where is he?

159
00:10:11,477 --> 00:10:13,535
Is he staying at Mr. Boon's?

160
00:10:13,560 --> 00:10:16,660
But they said
he came back home last week.

161
00:10:16,685 --> 00:10:17,686
Really?

162
00:10:19,280 --> 00:10:22,283
Then why didn't he come
to the volleyball practice?

163
00:10:24,940 --> 00:10:26,153
Hey, Thai!

164
00:10:35,992 --> 00:10:36,992
Thai.

165
00:10:38,889 --> 00:10:41,223
Son, your friends are here.

166
00:10:50,914 --> 00:10:52,576
I was assaulted.

167
00:10:58,600 --> 00:11:02,217
Everyone, when we're done,
I have a new movie for us to watch.

168
00:11:02,242 --> 00:11:03,318
- Really?
- Yeah.

169
00:11:03,343 --> 00:11:06,139
At first, when I just moved in...

170
00:11:06,164 --> 00:11:07,200
Eat up, Thai.

171
00:11:07,225 --> 00:11:09,916
He and his wife
took very good care of us.

172
00:11:10,682 --> 00:11:12,960
We had three meals a day.

173
00:11:12,985 --> 00:11:15,914
- Thai, eat up.
- Tomatoes for you skin.

174
00:11:15,939 --> 00:11:17,632
We had a safe place to sleep.

175
00:11:17,632 --> 00:11:19,223
Cover yourself up well, Thai.

176
00:11:20,371 --> 00:11:23,043
It's cold.
You'll catch pneumonia.

177
00:11:26,184 --> 00:11:27,904
How was your day? Tired?

178
00:11:28,600 --> 00:11:29,600
Yes.

179
00:11:30,242 --> 00:11:33,150
Get plenty of sleep.
We'll practice again tomorrow.

180
00:11:34,280 --> 00:11:35,716
Yes, Teacher.

181
00:11:41,415 --> 00:11:43,696
He trained us well.

182
00:11:44,840 --> 00:11:46,743
And even helped find us jobs.

183
00:11:48,885 --> 00:11:51,680
Many of us were very talented,

184
00:11:51,705 --> 00:11:53,295
and got gigs often.

185
00:11:53,320 --> 00:11:57,335
We earned good money,
enough to send some back home.

186
00:11:57,360 --> 00:11:58,667
Think about it.

187
00:11:58,667 --> 00:12:01,340
It was like being
in a boarding school

188
00:12:01,364 --> 00:12:03,096
but you also got paid.

189
00:12:03,120 --> 00:12:04,810
We were so happy.

190
00:12:04,834 --> 00:12:06,520
It was like a dream.

191
00:12:07,240 --> 00:12:09,760
Tuck yourself in. It gets cold.

192
00:12:09,785 --> 00:12:11,771
- Eat up, Thai.
- Yes.

193
00:12:21,414 --> 00:12:23,380
- Memorize the lyrics.
- Yes.

194
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:26,116
Until one evening...

195
00:12:26,960 --> 00:12:30,640
He called me in
to practice in his office.

196
00:12:37,266 --> 00:12:40,179
I remember because
he praised me for being a good boy.

197
00:12:40,204 --> 00:12:41,520
Said I sang very well.

198
00:12:42,200 --> 00:12:44,130
He told me to listen to him.

199
00:12:44,680 --> 00:12:47,390
And I would have a bright future.

200
00:12:47,966 --> 00:12:50,476
But not to tell anyone
about our special practice.

201
00:12:50,501 --> 00:12:53,280
Or else others would
get jealous and dislike me.

202
00:12:53,280 --> 00:12:54,540
What are you eating?

203
00:12:55,895 --> 00:12:58,436
I felt that something wasn't right.

204
00:12:59,320 --> 00:13:02,310
But I saw the other kids
in the house looked happy.

205
00:13:02,848 --> 00:13:05,776
No one else seemed to be
going through that same thing.

206
00:13:07,760 --> 00:13:10,960
So I chose to stay silent
and started to withdraw.

207
00:13:12,049 --> 00:13:14,110
Hoping it wouldn't happen again.

208
00:13:19,272 --> 00:13:21,216
But he did it again.

209
00:13:38,869 --> 00:13:40,121
How do I look?

210
00:13:41,417 --> 00:13:42,673
Very handsome.

211
00:13:49,480 --> 00:13:51,480
But this time, I wouldn't take it.

212
00:13:56,569 --> 00:13:57,569
Thai,

213
00:14:07,040 --> 00:14:08,197
take off your shirt.

214
00:14:09,049 --> 00:14:10,275
Like before.

215
00:14:11,599 --> 00:14:16,440
- No, don't.
- Come on. It's okay.

216
00:14:16,840 --> 00:14:19,747
- Don't. No!
- Come on.

217
00:14:19,772 --> 00:14:20,798
No!

218
00:14:24,877 --> 00:14:25,885
Ouch!

219
00:14:26,568 --> 00:14:28,735
Mother Ubol, help me!

220
00:14:28,735 --> 00:14:30,120
What happened?

221
00:14:43,661 --> 00:14:45,080
And then his wife...

222
00:14:46,886 --> 00:14:48,840
She sent me back home.

223
00:14:50,920 --> 00:14:52,323
She said I...

224
00:14:55,154 --> 00:14:58,603
I assaulted him
and destroyed property.

225
00:15:01,311 --> 00:15:04,110
But she wouldn't press charges
because she pitied me.

226
00:15:06,840 --> 00:15:10,756
Before leaving, she gave
my mom a sum of money.

227
00:15:11,367 --> 00:15:13,334
Told her to use it
for my education.

228
00:15:13,334 --> 00:15:17,816
Tell Thai,
forget whatever happened here,

229
00:15:19,405 --> 00:15:21,223
or else,
I will report this to the police.

230
00:15:23,096 --> 00:15:26,583
Yes, ma'am. Please apologize
to Teacher Boon for me.

231
00:15:27,200 --> 00:15:29,025
Otherwise, my mom
would be in trouble,

232
00:15:29,050 --> 00:15:30,935
having to pay for damages.

233
00:15:30,960 --> 00:15:35,423
And she'd have me arrested.

234
00:15:37,470 --> 00:15:39,516
My mom was so sad back then.

235
00:15:40,484 --> 00:15:42,996
I didn't want my mom
to suffer anymore.

236
00:15:52,704 --> 00:15:55,696
So I chose never
to speak of it again.

237
00:16:03,377 --> 00:16:04,377
Hey!

238
00:16:24,066 --> 00:16:25,406
Oh wow, Ohn.

239
00:16:25,406 --> 00:16:27,899
Back so late, huh?

240
00:16:29,011 --> 00:16:30,743
Have you eaten yet?

241
00:16:33,320 --> 00:16:34,320
Oh...

242
00:16:35,670 --> 00:16:36,670
What...

243
00:16:37,725 --> 00:16:38,725
Hmm?

244
00:16:42,522 --> 00:16:43,522
What's wrong?

245
00:16:47,985 --> 00:16:49,122
My work...

246
00:16:49,901 --> 00:16:51,414
is fine.

247
00:16:51,448 --> 00:16:52,448
Mmm-hmm.

248
00:16:52,473 --> 00:16:55,368
They're going to
publish the first episode.

249
00:16:55,393 --> 00:16:56,395
Mmm.

250
00:16:56,420 --> 00:16:58,600
If the feedback is good,
we'll get to continue.

251
00:16:59,280 --> 00:17:02,280
That sounds good.
So what are you worried about?

252
00:17:05,846 --> 00:17:06,848
Hmm?

253
00:17:06,873 --> 00:17:07,909
It's about Thai.

254
00:17:10,404 --> 00:17:12,135
It's so vile.

255
00:17:12,160 --> 00:17:14,061
He's a teacher, an adult.

256
00:17:14,085 --> 00:17:15,980
How could he do this?

257
00:17:16,004 --> 00:17:18,840
This is exactly why
Thai quit singing

258
00:17:18,840 --> 00:17:21,200
even though he
used to love it so much.

259
00:17:23,280 --> 00:17:25,535
We should expose him.

260
00:17:25,560 --> 00:17:27,520
Get the revenge he deserves.

261
00:17:29,920 --> 00:17:31,880
It happened a long time ago.

262
00:17:33,560 --> 00:17:36,920
My life right now is okay.

263
00:17:39,200 --> 00:17:42,200
If it's really okay,
then that's good.

264
00:17:43,649 --> 00:17:45,152
But if not...

265
00:17:45,177 --> 00:17:47,570
We are ready to
help you with everything.

266
00:17:48,407 --> 00:17:52,626
If you want to take action,
I'm with you. Let's go all the way.

267
00:17:52,651 --> 00:17:53,791
Hmm.

268
00:17:54,300 --> 00:17:55,300
Thanks.

269
00:17:58,313 --> 00:18:00,153
But right now, I'm not even sure...

270
00:18:01,253 --> 00:18:02,693
if I want to expose him,

271
00:18:04,347 --> 00:18:07,107
or be involved with him ever again.

272
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:14,680
I feel so angry for Thai.

273
00:18:15,840 --> 00:18:17,415
If it were me,

274
00:18:17,440 --> 00:18:20,440
I'd ask Chon to help me expose him.

275
00:18:22,426 --> 00:18:24,536
It's hard to talk about.

276
00:18:24,600 --> 00:18:26,360
A sensitive issue.

277
00:18:27,240 --> 00:18:30,920
If you're going to do anything,
you have to talk to Thai first.

278
00:18:32,160 --> 00:18:33,160
Hmm.

279
00:18:40,933 --> 00:18:41,933
I'm going to sleep.

280
00:19:11,856 --> 00:19:13,776
Hello? What's up?

281
00:19:13,800 --> 00:19:15,040
Ohn...

282
00:19:15,064 --> 00:19:16,878
I'm getting goosebumps
just talking about it.

283
00:19:16,903 --> 00:19:19,128
What is it? Tell me.

284
00:19:19,153 --> 00:19:21,175
It's about Mr. Boon.

285
00:19:21,200 --> 00:19:24,583
There's someone named Terd
looking for Thai.

286
00:19:24,608 --> 00:19:26,770
Says he's a junior
from Rakang Kaew house.

287
00:19:27,480 --> 00:19:29,391
Apparently Thai left the Line group

288
00:19:29,415 --> 00:19:31,364
so he couldn't contact him.

289
00:19:31,389 --> 00:19:32,557
Terd, right?

290
00:19:32,581 --> 00:19:34,815
Why is he looking for Thai?

291
00:19:35,378 --> 00:19:37,606
- Maybe...
- He's gathering information...

292
00:19:37,631 --> 00:19:40,455
with his reporter friends.
He's going to expose him.

293
00:19:40,480 --> 00:19:41,480
Expose him?

294
00:19:42,240 --> 00:19:43,269
Do you know...

295
00:19:43,294 --> 00:19:46,895
Thai wasn't the only one
abused by that teacher?

296
00:19:46,920 --> 00:19:49,764
Terd is gathering all the victims.

297
00:19:49,788 --> 00:19:51,542
He's found quite a few already.

298
00:19:51,567 --> 00:19:53,455
How about this?

299
00:19:53,480 --> 00:19:55,997
I'll set up a meeting
with Thai at a restaurant.

300
00:19:56,022 --> 00:19:57,495
So he can meet Terd first.

301
00:19:57,520 --> 00:19:59,735
Then we'll figure out
what to do next.

302
00:19:59,760 --> 00:20:01,202
Good idea.

303
00:20:01,227 --> 00:20:02,800
Okay, see you.

304
00:20:06,993 --> 00:20:08,153
Want me to go with you?

305
00:20:09,000 --> 00:20:10,200
- Jee.
- Mmm-hmm.

306
00:20:12,594 --> 00:20:13,880
Thanks, Jee.

307
00:20:29,804 --> 00:20:30,888
Hello, Thai.

308
00:20:32,240 --> 00:20:33,440
Do you remember me?

309
00:20:36,377 --> 00:20:37,520
I'm Terd.

310
00:20:47,157 --> 00:20:49,046
The last time we met was at...

311
00:20:49,747 --> 00:20:51,050
Teacher Boon's, right?

312
00:20:52,853 --> 00:20:53,853
Yes.

313
00:21:06,796 --> 00:21:10,131
This is a draft letter
proposing to revoke his award

314
00:21:10,156 --> 00:21:12,010
that he recently got.

315
00:21:14,956 --> 00:21:18,053
At the end of the letter is a list
of former students he abused.

316
00:21:19,239 --> 00:21:20,465
So many of them.

317
00:21:26,520 --> 00:21:27,520
Whoa.

318
00:21:28,619 --> 00:21:30,459
It's not just one or two people.

319
00:21:32,040 --> 00:21:34,004
Even one person
shouldn't have to suffer.

320
00:21:34,029 --> 00:21:35,423
He was their teacher!

321
00:21:40,690 --> 00:21:42,640
What this person
we called "Teacher" did to us

322
00:21:44,000 --> 00:21:46,615
was grooming and sexual abuse.

323
00:21:46,640 --> 00:21:50,536
A person like this
deserves no honor whatsoever.

324
00:21:53,153 --> 00:21:54,153
Terd,

325
00:21:55,080 --> 00:21:58,523
can you let
your reporter friends handle this?

326
00:21:59,176 --> 00:22:00,254
Yeah.

327
00:22:00,278 --> 00:22:02,552
You've already gathered a group.

328
00:22:02,577 --> 00:22:03,865
Should we expose him?

329
00:22:03,890 --> 00:22:05,090
I intended to do that.

330
00:22:08,843 --> 00:22:10,600
So what do you want me to do?

331
00:22:13,813 --> 00:22:15,103
If you are okay with it,

332
00:22:16,740 --> 00:22:19,456
I want you to
join the victim group.

333
00:22:24,151 --> 00:22:25,806
What if I say no?

334
00:22:27,613 --> 00:22:28,784
I'd be disappointed.

335
00:22:29,800 --> 00:22:32,123
But I'd respect your decision.

336
00:22:39,757 --> 00:22:41,583
Do you remember that video?

337
00:22:42,693 --> 00:22:44,963
The one he recorded us.

338
00:22:47,993 --> 00:22:48,993
I remember.

339
00:22:51,212 --> 00:22:52,840
No, don't!

340
00:22:54,400 --> 00:22:56,583
That'll be a key evidence.

341
00:22:57,482 --> 00:22:59,479
I'm going to get
that video from his house.

342
00:23:00,830 --> 00:23:04,295
How are you going to get it?
Who would just give it to you?

343
00:23:04,320 --> 00:23:06,558
Yeah, and by now,

344
00:23:06,582 --> 00:23:08,855
wouldn't the tapes be all moldy?

345
00:23:08,880 --> 00:23:11,013
Wait, don't tell me...

346
00:23:11,890 --> 00:23:13,934
you're going to
break in and steal it?

347
00:23:13,959 --> 00:23:17,828
Isn't that too risky?
If you get caught, that's theft.

348
00:23:17,853 --> 00:23:20,783
Exactly. Aren't you scared, Terd?

349
00:23:22,280 --> 00:23:23,280
No.

350
00:23:24,360 --> 00:23:25,800
I have to do this.

351
00:23:27,320 --> 00:23:29,400
Those tapes are crucial evidence.

352
00:23:30,280 --> 00:23:32,570
This shouldn't happen
to anyone else ever again.

353
00:23:34,920 --> 00:23:38,840
If we succeed,
the victims will dare to speak up.

354
00:23:40,033 --> 00:23:43,336
And the abusers like him
will learn their lessons.

355
00:23:46,320 --> 00:23:48,480
You're the only one I thought of.

356
00:23:50,573 --> 00:23:52,370
Will you come with me?

357
00:23:59,895 --> 00:24:00,895
Yes.

358
00:24:01,960 --> 00:24:02,960
I'll go with you.

359
00:24:03,486 --> 00:24:04,486
Thai! Thai!

360
00:24:07,567 --> 00:24:08,815
If you go,

361
00:24:08,840 --> 00:24:10,016
we're going too.

362
00:24:26,080 --> 00:24:27,743
Here's the plan.

363
00:24:27,768 --> 00:24:31,643
We'll pretend to visit him,
and split into two teams.

364
00:24:32,237 --> 00:24:34,545
Team A is Thai and me.

365
00:24:34,569 --> 00:24:37,170
We'll look for
the tapes in his office.

366
00:24:38,246 --> 00:24:41,286
Team B is Chon, Ohn, and Jira.

367
00:24:42,086 --> 00:24:44,286
You'll be backup
in case anything goes wrong.

368
00:24:47,544 --> 00:24:50,500
Yes, just like that.

369
00:25:11,020 --> 00:25:13,480
Hello. Please come in.

370
00:25:33,416 --> 00:25:35,023
Hello.

371
00:25:36,336 --> 00:25:39,375
I remember you're
from Rakang Kaew, right?

372
00:25:39,400 --> 00:25:41,563
Terd and Thai.

373
00:25:42,573 --> 00:25:47,130
I'm Buts, Butsaba, his daughter.

374
00:25:48,013 --> 00:25:51,280
Back then, I was in
a boarding school.

375
00:25:51,280 --> 00:25:53,707
So I didn't get
to see you guys much.

376
00:25:53,732 --> 00:25:54,760
I see.

377
00:25:54,760 --> 00:25:58,912
Thank you for visiting him.
He is resting upstairs.

378
00:25:58,937 --> 00:26:03,975
Please put on a mask first
because he is easily infected.

379
00:26:04,000 --> 00:26:05,000
Please.

380
00:26:16,603 --> 00:26:17,603
This way, please.

381
00:26:28,198 --> 00:26:29,280
Father.

382
00:26:29,973 --> 00:26:31,191
Father.

383
00:26:31,880 --> 00:26:34,266
Your students are here to see you.

384
00:26:34,291 --> 00:26:36,150
Terd and Thai.

385
00:26:54,240 --> 00:26:55,280
Mr. Boon.

386
00:26:57,721 --> 00:26:58,721
I'm Terd.

387
00:27:01,662 --> 00:27:03,073
Do you remember me?

388
00:27:15,614 --> 00:27:16,720
Everyone,

389
00:27:17,837 --> 00:27:22,720
I've prepared some snacks and tea.

390
00:27:23,640 --> 00:27:26,624
You can go rest for a while.

391
00:27:26,648 --> 00:27:28,648
This way, please.

392
00:27:37,609 --> 00:27:38,840
Terd...

393
00:27:40,820 --> 00:27:42,280
Terd...

394
00:27:55,440 --> 00:27:59,713
- Ms. Buts, I'll...
- Terd, Thai...

395
00:28:00,575 --> 00:28:03,480
Please excuse me for a moment.

396
00:28:03,504 --> 00:28:05,535
I need to go check on my mother.

397
00:28:05,560 --> 00:28:08,159
She's not doing very well either.

398
00:28:09,014 --> 00:28:10,163
Ms. Buts.

399
00:28:10,772 --> 00:28:12,975
The snacks are ready outside.

400
00:28:13,000 --> 00:28:14,464
- Yes, please.
- This way.

401
00:28:24,240 --> 00:28:25,427
Who is that?

402
00:28:25,451 --> 00:28:27,670
Did Boonmala come to see me?

403
00:28:29,179 --> 00:28:31,459
- Hello.
- Hello.

404
00:28:33,253 --> 00:28:36,120
Thank you, sir, for coming.

405
00:28:39,146 --> 00:28:42,680
Mom, they were dad's students.

406
00:28:42,680 --> 00:28:44,536
Terd and Thai.

407
00:28:46,213 --> 00:28:48,450
She's becoming forgetful.

408
00:28:49,170 --> 00:28:50,560
Would you like some tea, Ms. Buts?

409
00:28:50,585 --> 00:28:52,005
- No, thanks.
- Okay.

410
00:28:54,185 --> 00:28:58,120
It's so nice. So many students.

411
00:28:58,793 --> 00:29:01,126
It really is.

412
00:29:01,720 --> 00:29:04,710
Dad fell ill
as soon as he got the award.

413
00:29:04,735 --> 00:29:09,177
And students like you
who come to visit.

414
00:29:09,202 --> 00:29:12,223
It's fortunate
that he got the award.

415
00:29:12,248 --> 00:29:14,528
So we have some money

416
00:29:14,552 --> 00:29:17,774
to help with the expenses
for Mom and Dad.

417
00:29:19,040 --> 00:29:22,520
Excuse me, where is the restroom?

418
00:29:22,520 --> 00:29:25,280
I'd like to use the restroom.

419
00:29:25,280 --> 00:29:26,480
Make yourself at home.

420
00:29:26,504 --> 00:29:28,382
- It's inside. Go ahead.
- Oh, okay.

421
00:29:29,181 --> 00:29:31,773
- I'll go too.
- Go ahead.

422
00:29:46,899 --> 00:29:50,093
Ohn, do you know where his room is?

423
00:29:50,118 --> 00:29:52,000
How would I know?

424
00:30:02,854 --> 00:30:04,027
It's locked.

425
00:30:04,052 --> 00:30:05,200
I don't think that's it.

426
00:30:08,823 --> 00:30:09,985
- Whoops!
- Whoops!

427
00:30:11,047 --> 00:30:12,183
I'm so nervous.

428
00:30:12,208 --> 00:30:13,834
I said I need to
use the restroom too.

429
00:30:15,080 --> 00:30:16,723
His room is this one.

430
00:30:17,526 --> 00:30:18,526
- Chon.
- What?

431
00:30:18,551 --> 00:30:20,990
You watch the door.

432
00:30:21,015 --> 00:30:23,000
- Me?
- Yeah.

433
00:30:39,765 --> 00:30:40,774
Uh...

434
00:30:41,843 --> 00:30:43,453
thank... you...

435
00:30:43,916 --> 00:30:45,480
Hmm...

436
00:30:53,224 --> 00:30:58,120
Thank you.

437
00:30:58,544 --> 00:30:59,544
Hmm?

438
00:31:00,577 --> 00:31:01,685
I...

439
00:31:01,710 --> 00:31:04,038
am...

440
00:31:04,772 --> 00:31:06,217
...sorry.

441
00:31:34,220 --> 00:31:36,640
Thai, are you okay?

442
00:31:38,080 --> 00:31:39,080
Mmm.

443
00:31:41,389 --> 00:31:46,160
I remember
he kept the tapes over there.

444
00:32:02,673 --> 00:32:03,806
What are you doing?

445
00:32:05,720 --> 00:32:07,320
The maid is coming!

446
00:32:10,695 --> 00:32:11,695
Hurry.

447
00:32:18,960 --> 00:32:20,143
There's nothing here.

448
00:32:21,481 --> 00:32:23,440
Let's split up and search then.

449
00:32:23,440 --> 00:32:24,527
Yeah, go.

450
00:32:36,648 --> 00:32:38,160
What are you doing here?

451
00:32:39,880 --> 00:32:41,432
Oh, looking for my glasses.

452
00:32:41,457 --> 00:32:44,917
I forgot my glasses. They're gone.

453
00:32:44,942 --> 00:32:47,399
So I got lost.

454
00:32:48,079 --> 00:32:49,356
Which way is the restroom?

455
00:32:49,720 --> 00:32:51,255
- The restroom?
- Yes.

456
00:32:51,280 --> 00:32:52,440
It's this way.

457
00:32:52,465 --> 00:32:54,815
This way?
Alright, going to the restroom.

458
00:32:54,840 --> 00:32:55,966
Keep it down, please.

459
00:32:55,991 --> 00:32:57,646
Ohn, let's go now.

460
00:33:11,699 --> 00:33:13,880
I can't stay here any longer.

461
00:33:13,905 --> 00:33:15,680
- Come on.
- Let's go.

462
00:33:15,705 --> 00:33:17,078
- Hey, wait.
- What?

463
00:33:17,490 --> 00:33:20,145
- We forgot Jee.
- Where is he?

464
00:33:21,520 --> 00:33:23,160
Oh, Jee.

465
00:33:24,320 --> 00:33:25,320
Where have you been?

466
00:33:26,172 --> 00:33:27,505
- How did it go?
- Not so great.

467
00:33:27,530 --> 00:33:29,475
Let's go. I'll tell you later.

468
00:33:29,500 --> 00:33:31,480
No need to explain anything.

469
00:33:31,480 --> 00:33:32,543
- Just leave.
- Go, go, go.

470
00:33:32,568 --> 00:33:34,685
- Wait, wait.
- What?

471
00:33:34,710 --> 00:33:36,160
What about Terd?

472
00:33:38,146 --> 00:33:41,436
Teacher Boon is talented,
virtuous, and worthy.

473
00:33:41,436 --> 00:33:43,028
He has done so much work.

474
00:33:43,817 --> 00:33:46,735
He's helped so many students,

475
00:33:46,760 --> 00:33:48,560
given them opportunities,

476
00:33:48,560 --> 00:33:52,423
a good life, a career,
and a bright future.

477
00:33:53,120 --> 00:33:54,160
Is that so?

478
00:33:54,160 --> 00:33:55,230
- Terd!
- But...

479
00:34:01,896 --> 00:34:04,830
We have to excuse ourselves now.

480
00:34:04,855 --> 00:34:06,735
We don't want to
disturb you for too long.

481
00:34:06,760 --> 00:34:08,650
We want him to get plenty of rest.

482
00:34:09,378 --> 00:34:12,560
Oh, I see. Thank you.

483
00:34:13,879 --> 00:34:15,039
Thank you.

484
00:34:36,600 --> 00:34:38,280
What? No tapes?

485
00:34:39,743 --> 00:34:40,743
Mmm.

486
00:34:41,083 --> 00:34:44,400
The room has changed.
And the tapes are gone.

487
00:34:45,299 --> 00:34:47,742
We almost got caught.

488
00:34:47,767 --> 00:34:48,960
The maid showed up.

489
00:34:48,984 --> 00:34:51,767
Gosh, my blood pressure!
I almost had a heart attack.

490
00:34:51,792 --> 00:34:54,762
We're not doing this again.

491
00:34:54,787 --> 00:34:59,183
We'll get arrested before
exposing or helping anyone.

492
00:35:00,280 --> 00:35:03,261
We're fine, aren't we?

493
00:35:03,286 --> 00:35:04,786
We wouldn't know if we didn't try.

494
00:35:08,589 --> 00:35:10,166
I'm sorry, everyone.

495
00:35:11,087 --> 00:35:13,056
I didn't think
it would go wrong like this.

496
00:35:14,880 --> 00:35:17,667
Seeing him at the house
made me feel sick.

497
00:35:19,965 --> 00:35:23,203
Hey, when I was stuck
in the room with him,

498
00:35:24,249 --> 00:35:26,666
I think I heard him say...

499
00:35:27,993 --> 00:35:29,233
Thank you...

500
00:35:30,255 --> 00:35:32,653
And he seemed like
he wanted to say something else.

501
00:35:32,678 --> 00:35:36,575
But in the end,
he didn't say anything.

502
00:35:36,600 --> 00:35:39,320
So I secretly thought
he might have wanted to say...

503
00:35:40,966 --> 00:35:43,166
Sorry...

504
00:35:45,644 --> 00:35:47,737
Or he might have just been thirsty.

505
00:35:49,000 --> 00:35:51,495
I was so frustrated.

506
00:35:51,520 --> 00:35:53,260
Seeing someone
who used to be so cruel

507
00:35:53,284 --> 00:35:56,290
lying there sick and helpless,
completely defenseless like that.

508
00:35:58,648 --> 00:35:59,880
It's a pity.

509
00:36:00,960 --> 00:36:02,935
But being sick is one thing.

510
00:36:02,960 --> 00:36:05,636
The evil things he did
are another, right?

511
00:36:05,661 --> 00:36:06,661
Two different things.

512
00:36:10,643 --> 00:36:13,430
So, without the tapes, what's next?

513
00:36:17,015 --> 00:36:18,770
I guess we keep fighting.

514
00:36:19,760 --> 00:36:21,990
Until one of us dies, I suppose.

515
00:36:38,635 --> 00:36:39,989
Come to think of it...

516
00:36:41,047 --> 00:36:44,793
People always hurt each other
in one way or another.

517
00:36:45,520 --> 00:36:46,876
You mean Mr. Boon?

518
00:36:48,560 --> 00:36:49,560
Kit.

519
00:36:50,726 --> 00:36:52,636
Who do you think killed you?

520
00:36:53,400 --> 00:36:55,080
Do you want to blame anyone?

521
00:36:55,800 --> 00:36:58,277
Partly, I blamed
those who bullied me.

522
00:36:58,277 --> 00:36:59,400
And the rest?

523
00:37:01,667 --> 00:37:02,667
What about you?

524
00:37:03,720 --> 00:37:07,009
All this time,
I just pretended to forget

525
00:37:08,912 --> 00:37:12,003
because I wanted
to live a bearable life.

526
00:37:14,949 --> 00:37:16,630
But I just realized...

527
00:37:18,533 --> 00:37:21,909
I never forgot what they did to me.

528
00:37:22,840 --> 00:37:24,066
So what will you do next?

529
00:37:26,479 --> 00:37:27,839
I don't know yet.

530
00:37:47,440 --> 00:37:48,880
Hello? What's up, Ohn?

531
00:37:50,480 --> 00:37:51,500
Thai.

532
00:37:52,473 --> 00:37:54,009
Mr. Boon passed away.

533
00:37:54,920 --> 00:37:56,338
Probably last night.

534
00:37:56,362 --> 00:37:58,362
The funeral is this evening.

535
00:37:58,915 --> 00:38:00,355
It's on the news.

536
00:38:02,330 --> 00:38:03,330
Thai...

537
00:38:04,111 --> 00:38:05,240
Are you okay?

538
00:38:06,600 --> 00:38:07,604
Uh-huh.

539
00:38:12,010 --> 00:38:13,280
Terd is calling right now.

540
00:38:14,127 --> 00:38:16,719
Okay. You go talk to him.

541
00:38:16,744 --> 00:38:17,800
Hmm.

542
00:38:21,480 --> 00:38:22,480
Hello?

543
00:38:22,840 --> 00:38:25,520
Have you heard the news?

544
00:38:27,959 --> 00:38:29,640
Just a moment ago.

545
00:38:31,880 --> 00:38:35,000
Do you have some time?
I need to talk to you.

546
00:38:43,241 --> 00:38:44,241
Thai,

547
